                            <comment id="428325" author="yujian" created="Tue, 17 Sep 2024 21:36:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stancheff&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stancheff&quot;&gt;stancheff&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
With either of the above two patches applied on the latest master branch, while building the codes with gcc-14 against kernel 6.11.0-061100-generic on Ubuntu 24.04, I hit the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;obd.c: In function &#8216;jt_pool_cmd&#8217;:
obd.c:5093:9: error: &#8216;__builtin___strncpy_chk&#8217; output truncated before terminating nul copying as many bytes from a string as its length [-Werror=stringop-truncation]
 5093 |         strncpy(fsname, param, fsname_len);
      |         ^
In function &#8216;parse_pool_cmd_args&#8217;,
    inlined from &#8216;jt_pool_cmd&#8217; at obd.c:5216:7:
obd.c:5080:30: note: length computed here
 5080 |                 fsname_len = strlen(param);
      |                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~
cc1: all warnings being treated as errors
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The above error is the only one that is causing build failure. Could you please incorporate the fix of the above error into your patch so that we do not need another patch to support kernel 6.11?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
